title: PML-N’s Rana Tariq wins PP-254 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 10 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz’s (PML-N), Rana Muhammad Tariq Khan has won the Punjab Assembly election from PP-254 Bahawalpur-X by securing 55,467 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Syed Zeeshan Akhtar of Jamaat-i-Islami Pakistan (JIP) who bagged 11,248 votes.
Overall voters’ turnout remained 45.29 percent.
